23
00:02:07,769 --> 00:02:10,223
Anyway, he says that
we'd be unwelcome here

24
00:02:10,316 --> 00:02:13,879
because this is a very
bicycle-friendly place.

25
00:02:14,324 --> 00:02:18,621
It... It isn't. It's the home
of Mercedes and Porsche.

26
00:02:18,754 --> 00:02:21,738
- And Germany... -
- Exactly.

27
00:02:22,696 --> 00:02:24,465
Germany...

28
00:02:26,207 --> 00:02:28,949
Germany is the cradle
of the automobile.

29
00:02:29,051 --> 00:02:31,332
The car was
actually invented here.

30
00:02:31,433 --> 00:02:34,012
It's the last place on Earth
you can drive a car

31
00:02:34,098 --> 00:02:36,798
as fast as it will go
on the motorway.

32
00:02:38,366 --> 00:02:39,894
- It's true.
- All true.

33
00:02:40,003 --> 00:02:42,863
This is a true fact.
This is a true fact.

34
00:02:42,948 --> 00:02:45,269
The Germans are
the only people on Earth

35
00:02:45,346 --> 00:02:48,589
who really know
how to make a car.

36
00:02:48,698 --> 00:02:49,949
This is...

37
00:02:49,995 --> 00:02:52,997
- It's a true fact.
- It's true.

38
00:02:53,589 --> 00:02:54,659
I'll tell you a story.

39
00:02:54,738 --> 00:02:56,387
There was a Mercedes engineer

40
00:02:56,479 --> 00:02:59,238
and a Jaguar engineer
having dinner one night.

41
00:02:59,379 --> 00:03:01,277
The Mercedes engineer
said, "Ve haf..."

42
00:03:01,316 --> 00:03:02,848
Forgive the accent.

43
00:03:03,285 --> 00:03:06,504
"Ve haf a quality test
at ze Mercedes factory."

44
00:03:06,590 --> 00:03:09,863
Every night, ve take a car
off ze line at random.

45
00:03:10,019 --> 00:03:13,051
Ve put a cat in it,
close ze doors.

46
00:03:13,090 --> 00:03:15,394
If... When ve come back
in ze morning,

47
00:03:15,605 --> 00:03:18,277
ve know the door seals
are vorking correctly

48
00:03:18,379 --> 00:03:20,067
"if ze cat has suffocated."

49
00:03:22,918 --> 00:03:24,386
Nah.

50
00:03:25,072 --> 00:03:26,871
The Jaguar engineer said,

51
00:03:26,973 --> 00:03:29,723
"We've got something very
similar at our factory."

52
00:03:29,824 --> 00:03:31,840
We take a car
off the line at random.

53
00:03:31,933 --> 00:03:34,293
We put a cat in it.
We close the door.

54
00:03:34,418 --> 00:03:36,238
And we know the car's
been built properly

55
00:03:36,301 --> 00:03:39,722
if, when we come back in the
morning, the cat hasn't escaped.

56
00:03:41,019 --> 00:03:42,073
That is...

57
00:03:42,191 --> 00:03:45,025
- True story.
- Yeah. True story.

58
00:03:45,519 --> 00:03:46,910
The strange thing is,

59
00:03:47,012 --> 00:03:48,933
it isn't just cars
that are built well here.

60
00:03:49,012 --> 00:03:52,129
- It's absolutely everything.
- Except wine.

61
00:03:52,262 --> 00:03:54,238
Yes, except wine. Sorry.

62
00:03:54,409 --> 00:03:55,589
Well, come on!

63
00:03:55,636 --> 00:03:57,917
- Now come on!
- You drink that stuff?

64
00:03:57,957 --> 00:03:59,379
Yeah.

65
00:03:59,540 --> 00:04:01,308
I wouldn't wash my hair in it.

66
00:04:01,409 --> 00:04:02,691
Are you sure?

67
00:04:02,762 --> 00:04:04,247
No. It is literally everything,
though.

68
00:04:04,271 --> 00:04:05,715
I mean, German soft toys,

69
00:04:05,785 --> 00:04:07,668
better than anybody
else's soft toys.

70
00:04:07,738 --> 00:04:10,144
Cameras, kitchen appliances.

71
00:04:10,199 --> 00:04:12,520
The Queen of England,
she's German.

72
00:04:12,988 --> 00:04:14,746
She is. That's why
she's still working

73
00:04:14,801 --> 00:04:17,758
even though she's a hundred
and forty seventeen years old.

74
00:04:18,105 --> 00:04:20,629
There is no word here
for "that'll do".

75
00:04:20,691 --> 00:04:23,931
There is no ambiguity
at all in Germany.

76
00:04:23,997 --> 00:04:26,129
You certainly see this
with films. Okay!

77
00:04:26,215 --> 00:04:28,644
The names you have
for American films.

78
00:04:28,707 --> 00:04:31,574
I've got some here.
Remember Airplane?

79
00:04:31,668 --> 00:04:33,183
- Airplane...
- Yes.

80
00:04:33,269 --> 00:04:35,152
In Germany, it was called

81
00:04:35,308 --> 00:04:38,863
the Unbelievable Journey
In The Crazy Airplane.

82
00:04:39,019 --> 00:04:40,988
That is a comprehensive title.

83
00:04:41,152 --> 00:04:42,339
- You know where you are with that.
- Yeah.

84
00:04:42,363 --> 00:04:43,951
What was Jaws?

85
00:04:45,620 --> 00:04:47,183
The what? The Weisse...?

86
00:04:47,363 --> 00:04:48,840
The White Shark.

87
00:04:48,965 --> 00:04:50,800
It should have been
The Massive Shark

88
00:04:50,863 --> 00:04:53,361
That Explodes Eventually.

89
00:04:53,613 --> 00:04:55,324
You know where
you're going with that.

90
00:04:55,446 --> 00:04:58,253
What was...
What was Basic Instinct?

91
00:04:59,323 --> 00:05:02,168
Just not, a brief glimpse of
Sharon Stone's Vagina?

92
