♪♪

103
00:05:20,621 --> 00:05:22,363
But before all that,
I'd like to talk

104
00:05:22,394 --> 00:05:24,792
about the original Honda NSX.

105
00:05:24,887 --> 00:05:26,494
We have a picture of it here.

106
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,957
When that car
was launched in 1990,

107
00:05:29,051 --> 00:05:31,004
it was considered remarkable

108
00:05:31,090 --> 00:05:33,637
because it was fast
and exciting like a Ferrari,

109
00:05:33,723 --> 00:05:36,090
but unlike a Ferrari
of the time,

110
00:05:36,207 --> 00:05:38,449
it was also incredibly reliable

111
00:05:38,543 --> 00:05:40,465
and very, very easy to drive.

112
00:05:40,527 --> 00:05:42,824
Honda killed that car off
12 years ago.

113
00:05:42,902 --> 00:05:45,715
But finally, they've come up
with a replacement.

114
00:05:45,816 --> 00:05:49,417
So I've been down to our
track... to see what it's like.

115
00:05:51,419 --> 00:05:53,473
This is it.

116
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:58,146
It costs £138,000.

117
00:05:58,380 --> 00:06:02,430
Around the same
as a Porsche 911 Turbo S.

118
00:06:02,995 --> 00:06:04,589
And it has the futuristic lines

119
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:08,464
you would expect
of a rare-breed Honda.

120
00:06:09,214 --> 00:06:13,808
Power comes from
a 3.5 litre Twin-Turbo V6.

121
00:06:13,971 --> 00:06:17,785
Backed up by a squadron
of electric motors.

122
00:06:18,144 --> 00:06:23,745
Together, they give
the NSX 573 horsepower.

123
00:06:24,714 --> 00:06:26,683
So you would assume
the performance

124
00:06:26,761 --> 00:06:29,519
is something to shout about.

125
00:06:30,136 --> 00:06:31,831
Now, if you ask Honda

126
00:06:31,909 --> 00:06:33,620
for the technical
information on this car,

127
00:06:33,652 --> 00:06:36,464
they will email you
a file so enormous

128
00:06:36,636 --> 00:06:38,433
that it actually
breaks the internet.

129
00:06:38,534 --> 00:06:42,027
And yet, nowhere in it does
it mention the 0-60 time.

130
00:06:42,074 --> 00:06:44,636
They simply refuse
to tell us what it is.

131
00:06:44,736 --> 00:06:48,127
I know 0-60 times are
irrelevant in the real world

132
00:06:48,175 --> 00:06:50,753
and they're rather childish,
but look, this is a supercar.

133
00:06:50,847 --> 00:06:53,167
It's top trumps, isn't it?
It's important.

134
00:06:53,269 --> 00:06:56,597
So I'm gonna find out what
it is for you using this.

135
00:06:56,706 --> 00:06:58,852
It is a data-o-logger.

136
00:07:02,730 --> 00:07:05,105
Right. Put it in Track mode.

137
00:07:05,316 --> 00:07:06,902
Here we go. Launch control.

138
00:07:06,988 --> 00:07:09,152
Foot on the brake.
Mash the pedal.

139
00:07:17,264 --> 00:07:18,732
Phwoarh!

140
00:07:22,816 --> 00:07:24,769
I'm not sure that was
quite as neck-snapping

141
00:07:24,801 --> 00:07:25,816
as a Nissan GTR,

142
00:07:25,870 --> 00:07:27,781
but it wasn't far off.

143
00:07:28,183 --> 00:07:29,909
Let's see what I did.

144
00:07:32,206 --> 00:07:35,295
3.2 seconds 0-60.

145
00:07:35,409 --> 00:07:41,667
Which means... it isn't quite
as fast as a McLaren 570S,

146
00:07:41,769 --> 00:07:44,532
or a 911 Turbo S,

147
00:07:44,761 --> 00:07:47,214
or a Ferrari 488 GTB.

148
00:07:47,261 --> 00:07:48,995
That's why they're
not mentioning it.

149
00:07:50,722 --> 00:07:53,370
Honda is happy
to quote the top speed.

150
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:57,601
Which is 191 miles an hour.

151
00:07:57,902 --> 00:07:59,636
But that too is slower
than its rivals

152
00:07:59,730 --> 00:08:02,925
from Ferrari, Porsche,
and McLaren.

153
00:08:07,183 --> 00:08:09,730
So has the new NSX got anything

154
00:08:09,792 --> 00:08:10,948
in the performance department

155
00:08:10,972 --> 00:08:14,519
that makes it rise above
its supercar peers?

156
00:08:16,597 --> 00:08:18,238
Well, yes, actually.

157
00:08:18,347 --> 00:08:21,066
Firstly, there are the brakes,
which are fly-by-wire.

158
00:08:21,091 --> 00:08:23,355
There is no physical
connection to the pedal.

159
00:08:23,447 --> 00:08:25,784
That's because they
have to harvest energy

160
00:08:25,870 --> 00:08:27,542
to recharge the battery system.

161
00:08:27,651 --> 00:08:29,347
It's a much cleverer
version of that

162
00:08:29,379 --> 00:08:31,190
than you get on the Porsche 918,

163
00:08:31,245 --> 00:08:33,956
a car that costs
five times as much.

164
00:08:34,065 --> 00:08:35,393
Then there's the hybrid system.

165
00:08:35,464 --> 00:08:37,261
It uses not one electric motor,

166
00:08:37,316 --> 00:08:39,284
as you might expect, but three.

167
00:08:39,386 --> 00:08:43,144
And the way it uses them...
is well good.

168
00:08:43,339 --> 00:08:47,183
♪♪

169
00:08:47,269 --> 00:08:48,284
The one at the back

170
00:08:48,355 --> 00:08:50,269
is the wingman
for the petrol engine,

171
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:53,601
filling the power gaps
when the turbos lag.

172
00:08:54,081 --> 00:08:58,792
This gives the NSX ballistic
pick-up at any speed.

173
00:09:01,386 --> 00:09:04,706
Look, instant shove.
It's lovely.

174
00:09:12,089 --> 00:09:14,644
But it's the two at the front
that are the real party-piece

175
00:09:14,745 --> 00:09:16,839
because they drive a wheel

176
00:09:16,941 --> 00:09:19,394
each totally independently
of each other.

177
00:09:19,488 --> 00:09:21,402
Which means this car has

178
00:09:21,590 --> 00:09:24,409
a sort of space-age
four-wheel drive.

179
00:09:25,456 --> 00:09:28,667
And that means
extraordinary things happen

180
00:09:28,753 --> 00:09:30,824
when you throw it into a corner.

181
00:09:37,425 --> 00:09:39,441
So, as you approach
a corner like this one,

182
00:09:39,566 --> 00:09:41,511
computers are
measuring the speed,

183
00:09:41,620 --> 00:09:44,995
they're measuring G-force,
steering input, and so forth.

184
00:09:45,027 --> 00:09:46,644
They're adding power
to the wheel

185
00:09:46,699 --> 00:09:49,394
or taking power away from
the wheel as it's needed.

186
00:09:50,524 --> 00:09:54,222
Then you get perfectly flat,
perfectly controlled corners.

187
00:09:55,331 --> 00:09:57,971
It is a bit like
driving a Honda Civic!

188
00:09:59,893 --> 00:10:01,291
There are people who would say

189
00:10:01,316 --> 00:10:03,550
that... technology
like this in a car,

190
00:10:03,613 --> 00:10:06,120
helping it feel secure,
will make it dull.

191
00:10:06,222 --> 00:10:07,941
But it doesn't feel dull to me.

192
00:10:08,145 --> 00:10:09,792
It feels tremendous.

193
00:10:10,917 --> 00:10:13,824
I'm going fast and I'm relaxing.

194
00:10:13,947 --> 00:10:15,749
What's wrong with that?

195
00:10:15,773 --> 00:10:18,574
♪♪

196
00:10:18,691 --> 00:10:20,620
But the futuristic
four-wheel drive

197
00:10:20,688 --> 00:10:24,019
isn't the only piece of
23rd-century engineering

198
00:10:24,081 --> 00:10:25,636
on the NSX.

199
00:10:25,737 --> 00:10:28,604
The aerodynamics,
for example, are so clever,

200
00:10:28,753 --> 00:10:30,800
they can cool all the motors

201
00:10:30,925 --> 00:10:34,308
while providing vast amounts
of grip-enhancing downforce

202
00:10:34,417 --> 00:10:37,058
to the front and rear wheels.

203
00:10:37,082 --> 00:10:39,244
♪♪

204
00:10:39,269 --> 00:10:41,316
And it does all this
without anything

205
00:10:41,394 --> 00:10:45,667
as old-fashioned
as huge wings and spoilers.

206
00:10:45,691 --> 00:10:49,613
♪♪

207
00:10:49,638 --> 00:10:53,566
♪♪

208
00:10:53,591 --> 00:10:57,230
♪♪

209
00:10:57,269 --> 00:11:00,159
It's not just the technology,
which is brilliant,

210
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:02,933
it's that that technology
is on this car.

211
00:11:03,011 --> 00:11:04,925
Yes, we have hybrid supercars.

212
00:11:04,995 --> 00:11:07,134
We have the LaFerrari,
the McLaren P1,

213
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,601
the Porsche 918.

214
00:11:08,626 --> 00:11:10,730
But they're in the
million-pound bracket.

215
00:11:10,831 --> 00:11:14,613
This is only an eighth
of the price of the LaFerrari,

216
00:11:14,683 --> 00:11:16,909
and it's actually cleverer.

217
00:11:18,447 --> 00:11:19,490
I love this.

218
00:11:19,565 --> 00:11:22,644
I love the way it looks.
I love the sounds it makes.

219
00:11:22,792 --> 00:11:25,167
I like the sophistication
of the hybrid drive.

220
00:11:25,284 --> 00:11:26,644
I like the performance.

221
00:11:26,745 --> 00:11:29,364
I like the steering.
I like the interior.

222
00:11:29,558 --> 00:11:30,777
I really, really like it.

223
00:11:30,802 --> 00:11:33,581
And I find myself
wanting one quite badly.

224
00:11:37,769 --> 00:11:40,409
The original NSX made
owning a supercar

225
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:43,245
less painful and less expensive.

226
00:11:43,409 --> 00:11:47,863
This has done the same
for the hybrid supercar.

227
00:11:47,995 --> 00:11:52,152
It really is a worthy successor.

228
00:12:04,699 --> 00:12:06,550
James, Honda...

229
00:12:06,949 --> 00:12:10,480
Honda took ten years
to develop that car.

230
00:12:10,597 --> 00:12:11,558
And?

231
00:12:11,583 --> 00:12:13,847
Ten years is an enormous
amount of time

232
00:12:13,917 --> 00:12:14,980
to do a car.

233
00:12:15,074 --> 00:12:16,456
You can't criticise something

234
00:12:16,511 --> 00:12:18,769
because people spent
too long on it.

235
00:12:18,941 --> 00:12:21,339
People aren't gonna say "I'm not
gonna look round Cologne Cathedral."

236
00:12:21,363 --> 00:12:23,443
They took 600 years
to build it!"

237
00:12:23,510 --> 00:12:25,136
Ooh.

238
00:12:25,278 --> 00:12:27,414
Anyway, I love it.
I love that car.

239
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:29,058
Anyway, look, we've heard

240
00:12:29,097 --> 00:12:30,706
what you've got to say
about the NSX.

241
00:12:30,825 --> 00:12:32,699
Now it's time to hand it over

242
00:12:32,745 --> 00:12:34,316
to a man who thinks that...

243
00:12:34,441 --> 00:12:37,175
Well, potted plants
are a Communist plot.

244
00:12:37,472 --> 00:12:40,464
Yep. Here he comes.
It's the American!

245
00:12:43,856 --> 00:12:48,501
Come to England.
Shit weather. Shit beer.

246
00:12:48,817 --> 00:12:50,570
And he's off!

247
00:12:50,653 --> 00:12:53,396
Clearly in a tremendous mood.

248
00:12:53,505 --> 00:12:55,608
But it is very wet out there.

249
00:12:55,675 --> 00:12:57,310
Wipers flapping away

250
00:12:57,377 --> 00:13:00,478
as he powers onto
the Isn't Straight.

251
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:01,892
Looking good.

252
00:13:02,010 --> 00:13:03,102
Where I come from,

253
00:13:03,127 --> 00:13:05,220
this thing's badge
is inaccurate.

254
00:13:05,486 --> 00:13:07,470
Kind of like a loser's Cadillac.

255
00:13:07,627 --> 00:13:09,588
And yet, strangely,
we're still waiting

256
00:13:09,674 --> 00:13:12,119
for Cadillac's hybrid supercar.

257
00:13:12,306 --> 00:13:14,697
Right, now,
flying into Your Name Here,

258
00:13:14,783 --> 00:13:17,767
this really is a good day
to have four-wheel drive.

