00:53:02,911 --> 00:53:05,883
Ummm Yes. And his food.

1017
00:53:06,715 --> 00:53:09,365
Oh! That's my own urine!

1018
00:53:11,482 --> 00:53:14,302
- Are you two doing this?
- Yes, he is!

1019
00:53:14,372 --> 00:53:17,247
I'd get out of the way
if I were you.

1020
00:53:17,833 --> 00:53:19,818
The trouble with the chicken
is, it moves around,

1021
00:53:19,904 --> 00:53:21,341
making this a...

1022
00:53:23,318 --> 00:53:25,138
- Oh, good idea!
- Isn't it!

1023
00:53:29,073 --> 00:53:31,161
Right, reloading, James.
Reloading.

1024
00:53:31,325 --> 00:53:32,731
Oh, yes!

1025
00:53:44,184 --> 00:53:46,815
- Good shot.
- Not bad, was it?

1026
00:53:47,884 --> 00:53:50,252
Sort of game over now, really.

1027
00:53:50,481 --> 00:53:51,482
Hm.

1028
00:53:52,923 --> 00:53:54,224
Right...

1029
00:53:56,932 --> 00:53:58,705
It wasn't game over, though,

1030
00:53:58,955 --> 00:54:00,971
because I went back
to the drawing board

1031
00:54:01,057 --> 00:54:02,940
and started again.

1032
00:54:05,190 --> 00:54:07,453
Three months' work.

1033
00:54:07,659 --> 00:54:09,971
I've used the same basic
interior set-up,

1034
00:54:10,065 --> 00:54:12,674
but I've completely re-thought
the armour plating,

1035
00:54:12,768 --> 00:54:15,182
so that whatever
those two have...

1036
00:54:22,850 --> 00:54:26,170
Now, this is a Scimitar
light reconnaissance tank.

1037
00:54:26,248 --> 00:54:30,670
It's small, it's quite fast,
and it's quite manoeuvrable.

1038
00:54:30,868 --> 00:54:33,787
Its job is to skip around
the battlefield like a goat

1039
00:54:33,850 --> 00:54:35,592
and find stuff.

1040
00:54:39,803 --> 00:54:42,459
Now, look at Hammond, running
around in a mad panic.

1041
00:54:42,529 --> 00:54:45,131
He thinks I'm gonna
shoot him, but I'm not.

1042
00:54:45,240 --> 00:54:48,685
I'm just here
to mark him with a laser.

1043
00:54:49,310 --> 00:54:50,881
He's gonna shoot him.

1044
00:54:57,678 --> 00:55:01,014
Yes, this is a Challenger 2
main battle tank.

1045
00:55:03,037 --> 00:55:05,545
And this really is
a bug-out vehicle.

1046
00:55:05,624 --> 00:55:06,851
It's certainly a lot better
than, I don't know,

1047
00:55:06,875 --> 00:55:10,115
a Hyundai with spikes
on the wheels.

1048
00:55:10,787 --> 00:55:14,379
It'll totally protect its
occupants from... radiation,

1049
00:55:14,412 --> 00:55:16,714
nuclear fallout, gas,

1050
00:55:17,037 --> 00:55:20,384
even a direct hit, thanks
to its incredible armour,

1051
00:55:20,490 --> 00:55:23,490
from any known
battlefield weapon.

1052
00:55:24,962 --> 00:55:26,817
Then there's this gun,
which is...

1053
00:55:26,919 --> 00:55:29,694
there's no other word...
enormous!

1054
00:55:29,760 --> 00:55:31,263
120mm.

1055
00:55:31,669 --> 00:55:33,152
And it could hit a target...

1056
00:55:33,177 --> 00:55:36,349
let's say
Richard Hammond's van...

1057
00:55:36,536 --> 00:55:40,755
while the tank itself is doing
30mph over rough ground.

1058
00:55:42,263 --> 00:55:45,661
I think, though, today
I shall fire while stationary

1059
00:55:45,833 --> 00:55:47,945
because I want to
savour the moment.

1060
00:55:48,068 --> 00:55:51,029
OK, thank you, chaps.
If we could stop there...

1061
00:55:51,122 --> 00:55:52,182
Right, going down.

1062
00:55:52,311 --> 00:55:53,958
Roger. Going down.

1063
00:55:57,254 --> 00:55:58,656
Oh, dear!

1064
00:56:01,122 --> 00:56:04,536
I've loaded the gun with
a high-explosive shell.

1065
00:56:04,896 --> 00:56:06,443
It's a tracer shell,
so we'll be able

1066
00:56:06,552 --> 00:56:07,716
to monitor its progress

1067
00:56:07,755 --> 00:56:10,568
as it arcs toward the target.

1068
00:56:10,747 --> 00:56:13,052
Oh, Commander Clarkson,
this is fantastic!

1069
00:56:13,138 --> 00:56:15,529
I can see him right there.
Have you got him?

1070
00:56:15,638 --> 00:56:16,904
Yeah.

1071
00:56:18,450 --> 00:56:19,755
You bastards!

1072
00:56:19,880 --> 00:56:22,177
Oh, just put him out
of his misery, will you?

1073
00:56:22,355 --> 00:56:24,888
- Fire!
- Thud.

1074
00:56:38,154 --> 00:56:43,083
I'm not sure his bug-out
vehicle was quite as strong

1075
00:56:43,138 --> 00:56:45,388
as he may have
led you to believe.

1076
00:56:49,638 --> 00:56:51,072
Right...

1077
00:57:01,169 --> 00:57:02,442
Many months later,

1078
00:57:02,536 --> 00:57:05,294
I was ready to unveil
my third attempt...

1079
00:57:07,304 --> 00:57:09,342
an impregnable fortress.

1080
00:57:11,846 --> 00:57:13,081
Oh, yeah!

1081
00:57:15,228 --> 00:57:17,130
This is bug-out heaven!

1082
00:57:18,244 --> 00:57:20,583
I've used as my inspiration

1083
00:57:20,979 --> 00:57:23,635
the armoured personnel
carrier from Aliens,

1084
00:57:23,916 --> 00:57:27,330
on the basis that if it can
protect Sigourney Weaver

1085
00:57:27,447 --> 00:57:30,315
from that metal bitey
thing with teeth,

1086
00:57:30,510 --> 00:57:34,268
it can keep me safe from
Jeremy Clarkson and James May.

1087
00:57:34,471 --> 00:57:38,596
Underneath this beast are the basic
elements of an Alvis Stalwart.

1088
00:57:38,752 --> 00:57:41,658
So it was already
armour-plated, amphibious,

1089
00:57:41,783 --> 00:57:43,088
massively powerful,

1090
00:57:43,211 --> 00:57:46,048
six-wheel drive
and four-wheel steering.

1091
00:57:51,487 --> 00:57:54,605
And what I've gone and done
is improve it.

1092
00:58:02,893 --> 00:58:06,479
It's got a honeycombed
lattice work

1093
00:58:06,565 --> 00:58:08,643
of ceramic-steel
armour plating.

1094
00:58:08,776 --> 00:58:11,104
It's three times thicker
than the armour you'll find

1095
00:58:11,190 --> 00:58:14,932
on the turret of
an Abrams A1M1 tank.

1096
00:58:18,237 --> 00:58:23,118
In testing, I fired a 7.62
round at that hull,

1097
00:58:23,143 --> 00:58:26,908
and all it left
was a mark... like that one.

1098
00:58:27,785 --> 00:58:29,518
This thing is incredible.

1099
00:58:34,284 --> 00:58:37,292
Whatever those two
are planning this time,

1100
00:58:37,471 --> 00:58:38,870
it won't work.

1101
00:58:39,026 --> 00:58:42,643
They won't be able
to damage my soup now.

1102
00:58:47,561 --> 00:58:49,108
Drone feed stabilised.

1103
00:58:49,264 --> 00:58:51,084
Vehicle spotted in the open.

1104
00:58:51,280 --> 00:58:53,764
45 stand by to engage target.

1105
00:58:53,926 --> 00:58:55,928
45 stood to engage target.

1106
00:59:05,006 --> 00:59:08,186
This shell...
is twice as powerful

1107
00:59:08,295 --> 00:59:12,295
as the shell we fired...
from the tank.

1108
00:59:12,449 --> 00:59:16,397
And it can hit a target...
13 miles away.

1109
00:59:20,703 --> 00:59:22,237
Loading weapon.

1110
00:59:29,905 --> 00:59:31,780
Hot room, gun loaded.
Gun ready.

1111
00:59:31,805 --> 00:59:32,817
Fire mission,

1112
00:59:32,842 --> 00:59:37,881
target number
Uniform Tango 1805.

1113
00:59:37,991 --> 00:59:39,936
Altitude 35.

1114
00:59:40,028 --> 00:59:43,123
Direction 4600.

1115
00:59:43,241 --> 00:59:48,116
Gun target line 130.
Ready 68.

1116
00:59:48,241 --> 00:59:49,686
Command approve.

1117
00:59:49,850 --> 00:59:51,647
45. Engage.

1118
00:59:51,826 --> 00:59:55,194
Command approve. 45. Fire.

1119
01:00:01,053 --> 01:00:04,741
They're bored. They've
realised I'm unhurtable...

1120
01:00:06,191 --> 01:00:07,593
and given up.

1121
01:00:08,600 --> 01:00:10,326
Five seconds to impact.

1122
01:00:10,514 --> 01:00:11,890
They probably think
it's really funny.

1123
01:00:11,914 --> 01:00:14,116
They probably think
I'm out here all...

1124
01:00:24,016 --> 01:00:26,234
45. Target destroyed.

1125
01:00:36,595 --> 01:00:38,095
Yeah.

1126
01:00:40,337 --> 01:00:41,903
Now,

1127
01:00:42,348 --> 01:00:44,775
we went through
the wreckage afterwards

1128
01:00:44,842 --> 01:00:48,739
and this is all that remains
of Richard Hammond.

1129
01:00:48,793 --> 01:00:50,628
He's just dust,
and we know it is Hammond

1130
01:00:50,653 --> 01:00:53,784
because we found this
suspiciously white tooth...

1131
01:00:55,155 --> 01:00:56,624
in it. That's...

1132
01:00:57,851 --> 01:01:00,591
- That's him.
- That's him.

1133
01:01:02,231 --> 01:01:04,864
So, there you are, preppers.

1134
01:01:04,966 --> 01:01:07,903
The tragic remains of Richard
Hammond are proof positive

1135
01:01:08,028 --> 01:01:10,692
that your hobby is
utterly pointless.

1136
01:01:10,868 --> 01:01:13,809
- You spilled him!
- Spilt him on the floor.

1137
01:01:14,192 --> 01:01:15,762
Now you've got him
all over your shoes.

1138
01:01:15,863 --> 01:01:17,729
I know. Even when he's dust,
he's annoying.

1139
01:01:17,875 --> 01:01:19,343
Anyway...

1140
01:01:19,509 --> 01:01:21,044
On that terrible disappointment,

1141
01:01:21,091 --> 01:01:22,727
it is time to end.

1142
01:01:23,208 --> 01:01:24,567
He's pretty much gone now.

1143
01:01:24,592 --> 01:01:25,707
Thank you very much
for watching.

1144
01:01:25,731 --> 01:01:27,333
See you next time. Goodbye!

